76561197980238865,Not Recommended,248860,13081675,"Posted: 25 November, 2014",all,Blarghalt,"This game is *almost* good, but like many roguelikes I've seen come around, the devs ultimately seemed more concerned with making the game hard than making the game fun. Most interactions with this game are like this:Player: Oh boy, I found a gun!NEO Scavenger: But you didn't find any clothes in the first two turns, so I'm going to have to kill you.or:Player: Oh boy, clothes *and* guns!NEO Scavenger: Guess what? Disease time! Have fun dying from something completely out of your control!I understand the need for realism, but there's a point where that has to bow to gameplay and NEO Scavenger just often kills the player out of nowhere and pisses away a few hours of progress. Oh yeah, this game is permadeath-only, which already alienates everyone who actually likes not losing hours of progress due to unfair BS.There should be challenges, yes, but the player should never be put in a unwinnable situation if they themselves weren't the ones who put themselves in it. I'd be a bit more forgiving if this game HAD A PROPER SAVE SYSTEM, but since it doesn't, I can't forgive it for destroying several playthroughs simply because I rolled a bad number."
