,Not Recommended,248860,34026442,Posted: 4 August,all,calibrojosh10,"What I liked:Inventory managementA true survival style gameWhat You Need to Know:This game always sounded so good to me, making me want to play it but I never would buy it. I finally did and was ultimately disappointedThe game is turned based which isn’t where the game went wrong. Being turned based lets you think about actions and plan ahead while also giving lots of options in combat.This game is not meant to be what most people expect a survival game to be, where combat or mining resources is not the main gameplay loop. This again is not bad; it focuses more scavenging supplies and staying away from dangers, sounds good right?The game starts to fall apart when you play the beginning over and over not really learning from mistakes as it’s really the RNG that will hurt you. Combat is stupid in the sense that a lot of the time you just encounter an enemy, no warning or true way to avoid enemies. You try to run, but it fails a lot. So you get hit and bleed to death. This isn’t fun. I don’t want to fight random enemies if I stay hidden and cover my tracks and won’t let me run away even when I’m athletic carrying nothingThere are some games in this genre that do focus on a story(War of Mine) and some that don’t(Zomboid). Neo Scavenger said it has a story. I didn’t feel like it did. I didn’t find much in the game. I do know looking it up that it’s found through playing and not spoon fed to you. Some might like this, I didn’t as looking on the wiki anyway seemed like the story was short, sparse and barely even enough to keep me playing. I just didn’t find any reason to care about this world sense it felt so empty.Also having no real end to the game means that you real just play till you get bored, as you have no closure of escaping, sustainability, or actually surviving. I know it can be hard to do with the survival aspect as that might hurt replayability, but I think that is false. If the game is fun, you’ll want to play it again and try something newOverall having a hardcore survival game experience dependent on the RNG nature can mean that no matter how good you are at the game, a bad roll can mean you die and have to start the same 30 minutes over getting boring fast. The story is so bare that it does nothing to give you a reason to continue playing and with no ending to the game and I have more games to play that will hook me; I’ll pass for games with better survival mechanics.My Score:DPaid: $4Main reason for dislike:  replaying the beginning so much, no real end goal and RNG that hurts the vibeBetter games that are similar I recommend:This War of Mine (has an end, story and no zombies)Project Zomboid(no story, zombies, no end atm)Darkwood ( story, has an end)Sunless Sea ( great world, and story, weak combat, no zombiest, has an end)State of Decay 2 (might be cool)"
