,Recommended,248860,17479363,"Posted: 10 August, 2015",all,jeffix,"NEO Scavenger was on my wishlist for a long time, $15 seemed steep for a graphics/text game, let alone a rogue-like. Well, I got drunk one night and impulsively hit 'buy'. So now I have it, and I like it enough to give a review, which I don't usually do.NEO is brutal. This isn't the type of game where you play the ultra-altruistic ""Hero"" that saves everybody and looks good doing it. You'll live a lot longer if you take the attitude of ""desperate homeless guy that doesn't want to get involved in your♥♥♥♥♥♥quot;.When you die, it's over. No going back to a previous save. You just start over from scratch.The learning curve is a little bit steep, but so rewarding once you get there. My first several hours I went through at least half a dozen deaths. I learned to avoid fights. To clean my wounds before bandaging them. I learned to not ever eat yellow berries. I rage quit twice. I came back twice.Now, I've got a rifle (with ELEVEN bullets!), a warm coat and enough clean water to last me a week. I'm unstoppable, king of all there is in this wasteland.Except that I'm not. I still run away from everything that moves, I only camp in secluded buildings, diligently cover my tracks behind me and always keep an eye over my shoulder.And that's how it should be. I survived for this long because I learned how to live in the wasteland. I didn't get a bunch of XP from slaughtering hundreds of enemies and then suddenly become immune to a bullet to the brainpan.That's what I love about this game. The ""XP"" is your own damn brain. Learning how to craft the things you need. How to avoid those looters in the distance. Knowing that I've gotten as far as I have by not making mistakes.NEO has an outrageous amount of complexity that you would never know exists until you go looking for it. If you're on the fence, just buy it. Well worth the money spent.One last tip: If you're new, take botany. Makes the game a little more forgiving since you won't really have to worry about food & drink."
