,Recommended,248860,8802511,"Posted: 21 January, 2014",all,30phil1,"(This review has changed for the third time on 6/31/17)Being the first game I ever bought on Steam all those years ago, I feel like I should recommend this game. I already had written two seperate reviews in favor of it. So why do I feel like flipping that  big thumb upside down? Well, I've realized that this just isn't a good game. My issues with it just pile up when you actually look at it objectively. (Skip to the list now if you just want a brief overview without too much reading.)For starters, the RNG is ridiculous sometimes. I've had some playthroughs were I magically managed to kill one of the most powerful things in the game with nothing more than a hoodie and a stick. Other times, I take about three steps away from the start and a thing called a Mega Wraith comes by and slaughters me. Both of these things have happened at least twice.OK, lets say that RNGeezus is on your side and you managed to become an absolute tank. Now what? To be honest, I'm still not sure. I've got to the lengths of cheating the game and there's nothing else to it. You can go and do the story for a bit. A really small bit. I mean,you don't do anything in the story!No really, I've tried every dialogue choice and item combination allowed in the first ""encounter"" of the story. They all end with you being given a task -- a fetch-quest to get the ""Vase of McGuffin"" or something equally ridiculous -- that will either kill you if you're not a tank and bore you to tears if you can survive. Oh, did I forget to mention that it never tells you were the dang thing even is?! This is where my playthroughs tend to end.Last thing before I let the bulletpoints take over. Did I forget to mention this is as polished as a rusty machete? It's running in godforsaken,2005 Newgrounds,Adobe Flash for crying out loud! It also barely understands what a 1080p screen even is. I never noticed this for a long time but I used to play this exclusively on my laptop from... huh... it was from 2005 as well.PROS...- More in-depth than any other post-apocalyptic survival games I have ever played.- Kinda funny predicaments like getting your head LITTERALLY CRUSHED by something called a ""Mega Wraith""- Story is not necessary. Really, you can just jump in, not read anything and still have a good time. Great for when you don't have a lot of time to spend- Addicting. Beacuse you die so much, you constantly have that Flappy-Bird-ish, ""Just one more turn"" mentality (see CONS)CONS...- More expensive than I would like. Maybe thats just me but it just doesn't feel all that polished. In fact, it's still running in Adobe Flash!- Really hard. Since it's randomly generated, it takes a whole lot of luck to not die before you can even have a fighting chance.- Too much cussing in the main story. This might be my personal taste but some of the cursing in the game feels forced and unnecessary.- Ultimately pathetic story. If you do choose to play the main story, you'll eventually feel either A) disappointed with how it's handled or B) be completely and hopelessly lost. After the first meaningful encounter with the story, they pretty much give you the boot out of anything you might find helpful and pretty much tell you to do a fetch quest. A quest, mind you, that never once tells you how to complete it.I'm disappointed to have to turn my back on this game but I feel like it's just not good enough to recommend. Play the demo and leave it there. You've already played all the fun bits.30phil1 wrote a review30phil1 posted the review30phil1 played NEO Scavenger30phil1's head was crushed by Mega Wraith's grasp30phil1 died of trumatic brain injury*End Turn*"
