76561198028713287,Recommended,248860,32605005,Posted: 20 June,all,rosentrater5,"Neo Scavenger is one of those rouge-like games that comes off shallow with it's RNG ""BS"" and makes you feel like a toddler at first, but dont be fooled. After you gain some experiance and live for longer than a couple days you will realize how much depth all these interlocking systems have. The writing+ art + music is charming and at times can even give you one of the deepest feelings of hopelessness and lonesomeness only a realistic post-epoch game can give you. Its simple art style compliments the intense inventory management and crafting systems.My advice? Go in blind your first couple games until you get one long life. When that game eventually ends, crack open the wiki and start to really take advantage of every gameplay system. Pick the traits you think have the most benefits/crafting recipes, always look up the outcomes of random encounters, exploit the movement system (0.15 moves wont make you another spear, but it will let you move 1 more hex). You will get to see a lot of the game this way but just remember even with some of the best gear in the game, in the wrong conditions, one mistake can end your life.PSA: The dev is working on a MOBILE port! Very much looking forward to that :)"
