76561198024124203,Recommended,248860,29076753,Posted: 6 January,all,SpacemanSpiff,"Few games manage to create an atmosphere that's as creepy and demoralizingly nerve-racking as Neo-Scavenger. This is a scary game at bottom, but not ""thrill-horror""; things don't jump out at you. No, it has that horror of, ""Oh god... I know what's coming for me... I can see it a few miles off in the distance... and I can't do anything about it... I might as well keep pushing along and hope I can hide when it catches up."" That kind of horror.The music does a great job of adding to this atmosphere as well. Good music is hard to come by in games these days. Usually you find bland formless soundtracks, or stuff that just ""gets the job done"", but in Neo-Scavenger the music is an essential part of the experience.This is a very good adventure game with unique gameplay and a very original setting."
