,Recommended,248860,9688586,"Posted: 31 March, 2014",all,Clammy,"First off, buy this game. If you haven't already, then you've probably read the reviews and decided that this piece of work is too ""brutal"" and the RNG will screw you over at every turn. I'm sure you know a lot about how the game is from the store page description and the other reviews, but what I want to address are all of these ""LITERALLY DID EVERYTHING TO PREPARE AND EVERY SINGLE GAME I CONSTANTLY DIE INSTANTLY OUT OF NOWHERE! >:((("".1. No, you don't step outside of the spawn area and ""very commonly"" die immediately.2. This is a roguelike. It's advertised as an extremely difficult roguelike. You may as well go buy Dark Souls and leave an angry review when you die.3. It's actually quite the challenge to be constantly on the tips of your toes, and if you don't like that, don't buy the game and leave a bitter review.4. Though the supernatural aspects beg to differ, this gameistrying to offer you the most authentic and realistic experience of surviving in a wasteland.5. It's not DayZ. You won't find bandages every corner where you look. You will, however, find enemies that are equally as equipped as you and have the exact same amount of health, strength, and endurance. If you can land a lucky one-shot, so can they."
