,Recommended,248860,35074604,Posted: 19 September,all,Jimmy Rustle,"I pirated this game a very long time ago (no shame), and loved it to bits. I saw it randomly on Steam, a couple of years since the last time I played it, and was excited to support the game I had loved and have a nice pretty up to date and legitimate copy.(Minor spoilers ahead)The missions are the same every playthrough, and the map only changes slightly with each new save, but it doesn't get old. You'll develop your own playstyle over time, have your favorite skills and such. Some people like to rough it in wilderness, others like to chill with the Enclave, some like to head to Detroit and make a living off of selling scavenged goods to the marketplace. There are countless little details and different ways to approach situations using special items and skills in this game. Don't let the graphics (or the dozens of newbie deaths) fool you, this is an amazing game if you dig the realistic survival thing.Only cons I can really think of is that combat could be made a little bit less repetitive. Perhaps add some different verbage and some new kinds of wounds. But that's a very nitpicky thing."
