76561198004904434,Recommended,248860,13698829,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Anoose,"Wow. This game is absolutely fantastic! I've played many games over the years, and I can safely say that this one is the best I've ever played. It ticks all the boxes for me:1. It's challenging. A game without challenge is pointless. When you first start playing, you will get yourself killed multiple times, in a variety of different ways. This will keep happening unless you engage your brain, and use the tools available to survive. Permadeath means that you can't afford to make mistakes, which makes the game much more intense, and progression is much more fulfilling. I wouldn't have it any other way. 10/102. Gameplay. This game is a sandbox turn-based rogue-likeish RPG. Some may not like this sort of game, but I've played many games of this sort, and it's the best of the lot. Most of these sorts of games over-complicate everything, and gameplay suffers as a result. This is not the case for Neo-Scavanger! The sandbox element is the cherry on top - do whatever the hell you want to do. Perfect! :D 10/102. Focus is on gameplay and NOT on graphics etc. Too many games these days look nice, but in reality they have no replayability or depth. Neo-Scavanger is the opposite - the graphics and UI allow you to play the game, they are not there to be pretty . It's graphics and art are still great though, proper old-school stuff. Also, there is the added benefit that ANY computer will be able to run this game. It's built in flash, so if your PC can handle some random online flash game, it can handle Neo-Scavanger no problem. 10/103. Depth. This game is deep! I have been playing for a few days now, and I have barely scratched the surface. I've just about got the point where I can reliably survive in the wilds, and have yet to actually explore the world. The game is mysterious, it's hard to know what the game will throw at me as I continue to play, and I love that feeling in a game. 10/104.Lore and story. I like anything to do with post-apocalytic settings etc, who doesn't? I havn't really played enough to comment on this aspect of the game, but from what I've played so far the writing and story is top-notch. 10/105. Thoughtful developers who listen. Having read a few dev posts, it is obvious that they care about this game. They are very open to suggestions and discussion. 10/106. Mods. I haven't researched the mods much, but I know that they do indeed exist. Always great to have that option!Summary: 11/10. Buy this game now! Even if you normally don't like this sort of game, give it a go! It's cheap ;)"
,Recommended,248860,8625322,"Posted: 8 January, 2014",all,LeBoost,"I love this game. It's a lot of fun, and the writing for events is great! This game's mechanics have a steep learning curve, but is just fun after. The combat shows realism, and encourages not beating to death everyone, but rather beating up, trying to make surrender, or even kill with a ranged weapon. Also, the skills are useful. For a example, if your tired of freezing to death, get trapping. You can make a campfire from friction. Also, the current special areas are amazing, and have quite a bit hidden surprises. (There is even a haunted house!) Go play this game, it's just 10.00 US dollars, and is worth even more than that. It requires scavenging a lot, and the name live up to it. For those preferring strategic turn-based games, buy this."
