76561197986443427,Recommended,248860,22735977,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Rackminster,"You wake up in a cryo facility, a slavering beast is approaching.  You're a skilled Mechanic, and you override the door mechanism, locking it out.  You step outside into a barren wasteland, a glow on the horizon to the East.  Somewhere, a pack of dogs howl, and they're getting closer.  You run for shelter and find a monkey wrench.  You put up a fierce fight ...You wake up in a cryo facility, a slavering beast is approaching.  You're a skilled Athelete, and you spring out the window unscathed.  You step outside into a barren wasteland, a glow on the horizon to the East.  A scavenger approaches you, spear in hand.  The look on his face is pure desperation. You try and run away, but fall to the floor ...You wake up in a cryo facility, a slavering beast is approaching.  You're a skilled Botanist, and you find castor plants, smearing yourself with them and making your scent toxic to drive the beast away.  You step outside into a barren wasteland, a glow on the horizon to the East.  You make your way towards the glow, picking up a mismatched pair of shoes and dragging around two grocery bags filled with twigs, kindling, and empty water bottles.  You're close to hypothermic, but just need to survive until the next day so you can focus the sunlight to start a fire to warm yourself.  As dawn approaches, you slip into oblivion...You wake up in a cryo facility... Good luck!NEO Scavenger is a brutal game where you'll die often, and in horrible ways - even once you understand all of the mechanics, the random number generator will seal your fate if you're not very very careful (and sometimes even if you are).  There's surprising depth in the crafting, combat, and survival aspects for a game without any animation.  You need a tin can, a lighter, and some twigs to make sterile water to drink.  You need the same things plus a dirty rag to make a clean rag.  If you get hurt and are bleeding, you need to wash the wound with sterile water (or another antiseptic) and then bandage it with a clean rag.  I died of massive infections twice by the time I realized how to properly care for myself after a fight.  I died several times in combat before I realized how to play defensively and wait for openings.  I still die just through bad luck, but I'm getting further and further into the game each time."
