,Recommended,248860,9039549,"Posted: 9 February, 2014",all,RelicLord,"This game is a welcome throwback to the old style, where creating an atmosphere was more important than the pixel count of the cutscenes. Running a minimal gui and text-based descriptions of most events, the game manages to create a sense of urgency and intensity right from the first moments.This urgency stems from a sense of realism, not in the sense of arbitrary damage values or photo-realistic animations, but in the sense of hand-to-hand combat being a bloody and exhausting affair. I engaged my first human unfriendly (not to give too much away, beginning or no,) with a multi-tool knife thinking that my ""weapon"" easily beat his ""basic attack"" only to be surprised by tackles, ground fighting, and a desperate struggle that left me frantically kicking him to death rather than celebrating with some level-up mechanic. I realized that even though I thought myself armed, in reality a multitool is a terrible damn weapon. The realistic aspect here is simple and effective, and more than just the number crunching.At present build it seems like a few things could use tweaking or adding on to, but that's to be expected at this point and gives me hope that player input will keep this easily-overlooked gem on track. If the game were free, I would gladly still have donated just to see this game continue."
