76561197993301119,Recommended,248860,17732999,"Posted: 26 August, 2015",all,nickd007,"This game is brutal. It is unkind and unforgiving and sometimes it is straight up mean. Sometimes whatever God is left in the NEO Scavenger world decides that you looked at him funny, and so he introduces you to pain and anguish and misery. But in the event that God does not doom you to such a fate, you will find in this world amazing potential and unique adventures.You will learn what fear is. Fear will guide you away from conflict. Away from that man, from those dogs, from that Dogman. You fancy yourself a proud fighter? Proud men die. Fear will keep you on your toes, will check any scrape and cut meticulously, will get you home by nightfall.You will learn what hunger is. You'll find yourself starving, losing energy, panicking. Maybe you'll trap a squirrel for a snack. Or beat a feral dog to death for some real meat. Maybe you'll take a step back and wonder how things got this way - huddled in some burnt out building, greedily eating packets of ketchup and saltines, washing them down with questionable river water. You might even find yourself in an unthinkable situation. You might manage to hold your own against a bandit. He came upon you while you were sleeping and tried to loot your camp. You woke, and he punched your head in a panic. You stand and brandish a crowbar. He turns to run, but he trips. You seize the opportunity. You strike. Again and again. Soon his blood rushes from his crushed head. And only then do you realize how hungry you are.tl;dr buy it."
